laboratory_examinations.findings: The liver, spleen, adrenals, pancreas, and gallbladder appear normal. The kidneys demonstrate symmetric contrast enhancement and brisk bilateral excretion without hydronephrosis. The stomach is collapsed. Duodenum, and loops of small bowel are normal in caliber and enhancement. Contrast has reached the sigmoid. There is a dilated appendix measuring up to 13 mm, containing an appendicolith at its base, fluid filled with surrounding inflammatory stranding. No intraperitoneal free fluid or free air. The aorta is normal in caliber along its visualized course, its major branches are patent. No retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy. The colon has scattered diverticula, no evidence of diverticulitis.
